    <section id="foundations_paradigms">
      <title>Paradigms</title>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>Examples of effective strategies for building interactive
          systems provide paradigms for designing usable interactive
          systems.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>The evolution of these usability paradigms also provides a
          good perspective on the history of interactive computing.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>These paradigms range from the introduction of time-sharing
          computers, through the WIMP and web, to ubiquitous and context-aware
          computing</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>

