    <title>Individual Assignments</title>

    <section id="individual_assignments_quina_interface">
      <title>Quina Interface</title>

      <para>Construct a functional mockup of the interface for a system to
      generate bets for the Quina game. This system will run in a Palm OS PDA
      (Personal Digital Assistant), such as Palm or Handspring PDAs, and thus
      the mock up should use the Palm OS interface widgets.</para>

      <para>The scenery could be a bar or a restaurant where clients would
      have Palm OS PDAs available to them to make Quina games. When the
      clients ask their bill, the price of their bets would be added to their
      bill and they would receive the receipts of their bets.</para>

      <para>Remember:</para>

      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>Take in consideration the size of a Palm OS PDA when design
          your interface.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>You can make the mockup in any suitable language (Java, HTML,
          etc). However, you may get a better result using a Palm OS emulator
          (for Windows or Linux). If do not use a emulator, remember that you
          should use the Palm OS interface widgets.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>You have to worry only about the interface, you do not have to
          implement other parts of the system, such as the communication
          system for sending the bets to a computer terminal. The mockup
          should give a feeling of how the system operation will be, you do
          not have to implement the actual operations.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>Get a Quina ticket from a Loterica to know how it looks like
          and what options are available. Remember, your users are already
          familiar with its appearance.</para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
    </section>
